This is the available documentation for the ESPRESSO package:

manual.tex      User's Guide for ESPRESSO
                requires html.sty (from latex2html package): if not
                available, comment "\usepackage{html}" and uncomment
                "\def\htmladdnormallink#1#2{#1}"

refman.tex      Reference (technical) manual for PWscf: little more
                than a template at present

INPUT_FPMD      Input parameters for FPMD
INPUT_CP        As above for CP (possibly obsolete)
INPUT.HOWTO     Hints on how to choose simulation parameters for CP/FPMD with
                Car-Parrinello dynamics
INPUT_PW        Input parameters for PWscf (pw.x)
INPUT_PP        Input parameters for postprocessing (pp.x)
INPUT_PROJWFC   Input parameters for postprocessing (projwave.x)
INPUT_CHDENS    Input parameters for plotting (chdens.x)
INPUT_PH        Input parameters for phonon calculations (ph.x)
INPUT_Gamma     Input parameters for normal-mode calculations (phcg.x)
INPUT_D3        Input parameters for 3rd-order derivatives (d3.x)
INPUT_EFG       Input parameters for electric-field gradient calc (efg.x)
INPUT_NC        Input parameters for noncolinear magnetism (pwnc.x)
INPUT_PWCOND    Input parameters for ballistic conductance (pwcond.x)
INPUT_RAM       Input parameters for Raman calculation (raman.x)

ChangeLog       ChangeLog for the ESPRESSO suite - after aug. 2004
ChangeLog.pw    ChangeLog before aug 2004 for PWscf
ChangeLog.cp    ChangeLog before aug 2004 for CP and FPMD

BUGS            List of bugs fixed - only bugs that have been present
                in some "official" release are listed
CREDITS         Who did what

pwscf.png, pwscf.eps, democritos.png, democritos.eps
                PWscf and DEMOCRITOS logos -- included from manual.tex

